Description: Almost complete small seal-impression made of fine brown Nile clay that was hardened after excavation. The rear shows one side with basketry coil and a second flat side with plant fibres. The front side is covered in finger impressions that partly overlay and distort the seal impression which is otherwise completely preserved. It shows a standing falcon, facing to the left, behind it a standing bull, facing to the left as well, underneath a crocodile or a khpr with wings?
Findspot: Excavated/Findspot: Amara West (Nubia), E14.7 temple magazine
Acquisition notes: Formerly housed by the Birmingham Museum and Art Gallery and the EES London.
